menu "AIVMT Standardized-Patient"

    config AIVMT_PTT_ENABLE
        bool "Enable push-to-talk (PTT) hardware button for SP encounters"
        default n
        help
            When enabled, the host firmware creates a dedicated GPIO button that
            forwards press/release events to the SpSession encounter state
            (start/stop listening). Leave disabled for boards without a wired PTT
            button; the default build is unaffected.

    config AIVMT_PTT_GPIO
        int "PTT button GPIO number"
        default -1
        depends on AIVMT_PTT_ENABLE
        help
            GPIO the push-to-talk button is wired to (active-low). Set to the
            physical button pin on your board. -1 means unconfigured.

    config AIVMT_ENCOUNTER_POST_URL
        string "Local server URL to POST a finished SP encounter"
        default "http://CHANGE_ME_LOCAL_SERVER:8003/aivmt/encounter"
        help
            HTTP endpoint on the self-hosted local server that receives the
            de-identified encounter JSON (telemetry + transcript). Local-only by
            policy (patient confidentiality); no cloud fallback.

endmenu
